The '''''kar''''' is a vocal genre in [[Ottoman classical music]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Baily|first1=John|title=Music of Afghanistan: Professional Musicians in the City of Herat|date=1988|publisher=CUP Archive|isbn=9780521250009|page=13|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=uSE9AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA13&dq=Kar+(Turkish+music)&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj00v_5lobYAhVFK8AKHXMCDi4Q6AEINzAE#v=onepage&q=Kar%20(Turkish%20music)&f=false|accessdate=13 December 2017|language=en}}</ref> It was a movement of the ''[[fasıl]]'', or suite.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Music|first1=Garland Encyclopedia of World|title=The Concise Garland Encyclopedia of World Music|date=2013|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9781136096020|page=873|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=hzIt6ZL5lY0C&pg=PA873&dq=Kar+(Turkish+music)&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj00v_5lobYAhVFK8AKHXMCDi4Q6AEIUzAJ#v=onepage&q=Kar%20(Turkish%20music)&f=false|accessdate=13 December 2017|language=en}}</ref>

