'''Otto''' (died 643 or 644) was the [[mayor of the palace]] of [[Austrasia]] briefly in the mid-seventh century.

Otto was the son of a ''[[Domesticus (Roman Empire)|domesticus]]'' named Uro who served in the court of [[Dagobert I]]. Otto was raised with Dagobert's son [[Sigebert III]] and subsequently acted as Sigebert III's ''baiolos'' ([[bailiff]]?). On the death of [[Pepin of Landen]] in 639 or 640, Otto challenged the succession of [[Grimoald I|Grimoald]] to the mayorship. Otto was eventually murdered by [[Leuthard II, Duke of Alemannia]], at the request of Grimoald.

