{{citation style|date=August 2014}}
'''Well Told Story''' is a communications research and production company active in [[Kenya]] and [[Tanzania]] and based in [[Nairobi]], Kenya. It is best known as the producer of the multimedia youth communications platform [[Shujaaz]].
Well Told Story has received several international media awards for innovation in multimedia storytelling including two [[International Emmy Awards]] in 2012<ref>The Hollywood Reporter. [http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/digital-emmy-awards-well-told-story-kenya-femme-fatales-306659], ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'', Los Angeles, 1 April 2012. Retrieved on 10 August 2014.</ref> and 2014<ref>Harrison, Chris. [http://www.the-star.co.ke/news/article-170740/shujaaz-youth-engagement-wins-emmy], "[[The Star (Kenya)|The Star]]", Nairobi, 11 June 2014. Retrieved on 10 August 2014.</ref> and a [[One World Media]] Award in 2011<ref>One World Media. [http://archive.oneworldmedia.org.uk/fellowships/shujaaz/].</ref> for [[Shujaaz]], as well as an International Emmy Award Nomination<ref>International Academy of Television Arts and Sciences. [http://www.iemmys.tv/awards_nominees.aspx] The International Emmy Awards, Cannes, April 2013. Retrieved on 10 August 2014.</ref> and a One World Media Award<ref>One World Media. [http://archive.oneworldmedia.org.uk/awards/winners/digital-media/].</ref> in 2013 for "JongoLove", a story told in Kenya across FM radio, [[YouTube]], SMS and [[Facebook]].
