The '''''Établissement Français d'Enseignement Montaigne''''' ('''EFE Montaigne'''), or the '''''École Montaigne''''', is a French international school in [[Cotonou]], [[Benin]]. It has the levels ''primaire'' (primary) through ''lycée'' (senior high school).

Its origins stretch to 1951, when the ''cours Montaigne'' was created.<ref>"[http://www.efemontaigne-cotonou.com/spip.php?article4 Historique]." ''Établissement Français d'Enseignement Montaigne''. Retrieved on 19 January 2015.</ref> The school in its present form opened in 1984.<ref>"[http://www.ambafrance-bj.org/Ecole-Montaigne E.F.E. Montaigne]." Embassy of France in Benin. Retrieved on 19 January 2015.</ref>

